50|$|In the House of Lords, <b>Grand</b> <b>Committee</b> is {{a meeting}} of the House as a whole, but away from the Floor of the House. A <b>Grand</b> <b>Committee</b> {{operates}} similarly to a Committee of the Whole House, except that no votes can take place, so amendments must be unanimously agreed upon. House of Lords <b>Grand</b> <b>Committees</b> may consider Bills or statutory instruments (usually but not always instruments that later require approval on the Floor of the House under the affirmative resolution procedure), or debate particular issues or topics.|$|R
